# Income Credit Exposures Non Accrual Without Provisions Full Performance Amount

## identifier
de7755

## status
Standard

## type
undefined

## definition
This is the amount of any income actually received during the relevant period from all exposures of the reporting party that give rise to counterparty credit risk, determined in accordance with the relevant prudential standards, where the estimates of future interest income are zero; no specific provision for impairment has been raised in respect of it; and the reporting party is receiving full contractual payments.

## guidance
undefined

